cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically video rain/snow removal. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as sparse coding and maximum a posteriori estimation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach that considers dynamic statistics of rain/snow and background scenes, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper uses an ADMM algorithm to solve the proposed model, which could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
